The ANC wants the Political Party Funding Act to be amended. The Political Party Funding Act came into effect on 1 April 1 2021. Minhaj Jeenah from My Vote Counts speaks to #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Rights groups say they're appalled by attempts to amend the Political Party Funding Act. The cash-strapped ANC is proposing changes to the law that came into effect in April last year. READ: Political Party Funding Act | ANC proposes amendments It says political parties have less capacity to mobilise resources for their activities. The organisation hasn't paid its staff members for months. WATCH: Political Party Funding | Parties declare donations Among the proposed changes is to raise the annual disclosure threshold. But My Vote Counts says the law should only be amended if it is found to be unconstitutional. It says the existing law should rather be strengthened to prevent secrecy in politics.